                    <note>*Corresponding Author: Total number: Text Pages (10), Tables (0), Figures (2) Funding: No funding obtained Disclosure: No conflict of interest to disclose Precis: Herein we report the case of a molecular confirmed low-grade fibromyxoid tumor of mandible that recurred twenty years later as high-grade sclerosing epithelioid fibrosarcoma. While an extremely rare location, an awareness of this entity, and its potential for high-grade transformation, is warranted. Acknowledgments: The authors are extremely grateful for exemplary technologic support provided by Mr. Anthony Wing and Ms. Jasmine Wong (Immunohistochemistry), Ms. Martha Wood (molecular cytogenetics), and Mr. David Swanson (next generation sequencing).</note>
